The pair died on impact when the roof caved in while they were sleeping. JOHANNESBURG - The heavy rainfall in KwaZulu-Natal has claimed the lives of two people. A house belonging to a Durban couple collapsed on Monday night. The pair died on impact when the roof caved in while they were sleeping. Emergency services' Robert McKenzie: "A man and a woman both sustained fatal injuries after their house collapsed, which is thought to be due to the heavy rain that Durban experienced on Monday night." At the weekend, a boy died when he was electrocuted during a storm.